{"type":"message","id":"8c0ac1a4","parentId":"bbb7e340","timestamp":"2026-03-07T01:04:44.269Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"QMD works perfectly when called directly with `-c memory` or `-c workspace`. The issue is that `memory_search` tool in OpenClaw is calling qmd with `-c memory-dir-main` which doesn't exist. \n\nThe fix is to update the OpenClaw config so it uses the correct collection name, OR add a collection called `memory-dir-main` that points to the right place.\n\nWait, actually the `memory_search` tool is built into OpenClaw. It's using `memory-dir-main` as the collection name internally. This might be because when OpenClaw sets up its collections, it creates them with the name `memory-dir-main` for the main agent's memory directory.\n\n\nI need to figure out if I can change the QMD collection name in the config or if there's an OpenClaw setting that controls what collection name the memory_search tool uses. Looking at the openclaw.json, the collections are defined as `workspace` and `memory`, but the memory_search tool is trying to access `memory-dir-main` instead—this suggests either a naming mismatch in OpenClaw's implementation or a config key I'm missing. Let me check the OpenClaw documentation to understand how QMD collections are supposed to be configured.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"QMD works fine — the issue is just a collection name mismatch. OpenClaw's `memory_search` tool calls QMD with `-c memory-dir-main`, but the actual collection is named `memory`. Let me check the docs and fix the config."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01TJtn5SPMDkyovLuTbERfvM","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /usr/local/Cellar/node@22/22.22.0_1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs -name \"*.md\" | xargs grep -l -i \"qmd\\|memory\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":459,"cacheRead":17729,"cacheWrite":954,"totalTokens":