{"type":"message","id":"a0fd510b","parentId":"52ba12ce","timestamp":"2026-03-07T01:12:35.998Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `memory-dir-main` collection is no longer listed! It seems the collection was not persisted to the SQLite database. When I ran `qmd update`, it showed it indexed the files, but the collection data was not stored properly.\n\nLooking at the YAML file more carefully - the QMD config is in `index.yml` which defines the collections. The `qmd update` command should read from this config file and update the SQLite database. But when I run `qmd collection list` with the XDG vars, it now shows only the original 4 collections (without `memory-dir-main`).\n\nWait, I edited the YAML file to add `memory-dir-main`. Let me check if the edit was saved correctly.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01K8CFF6FXSVN74V6WZF9qJ6","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/agents/main/qmd/xdg-config/qmd/index.yml"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":253,"cacheRead":45321,"cacheWrite":337,"totalTokens":45912,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.003795,"cacheRead":0.013596299999999999,"cacheWrite":0.0012637500000000001,"total":0.01865805}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772845948194}}
