{"type":"message","id":"d167e537","parentId":"a56d542b","timestamp":"2026-03-07T01:12:50.064Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `memory-dir-main` entry I added is gone from the YAML! OpenClaw must have overwritten the file when it did its own QMD update (or the gateway restart regenerated it from config). So every time OpenClaw runs `qmd update`, it rewrites the `index.yml` from the `openclaw.json` config - and since `memory-dir-main` isn't in the `openclaw.json` paths config, it gets removed.\n\nThe fix needs to happen in `openclaw.json` — I need to add a path entry with `name: \"memory-dir\"` (which will become `memory-dir-main` with the agent ID suffix) so that OpenClaw creates and maintains this collection.\n\n\nLooking at the current paths configuration, I see `workspace` and `memory` entries that get the agent ID appended to their names. I need to add a `memory-dir` entry to the paths array to create the `memory-dir-main` collection, though I'm wondering if `includeDefaultMemory: true` should already be handling this.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"OpenClaw keeps regenerating `index.yml` from `openclaw.json` — so my manual edit gets overwritten. I need to add `memory-dir` as a named path in `openclaw.json` so it generates `memory-dir-main` automatically."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01BWunwzCg3DCUETLHeBcAFj","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -m json.tool | grep -A15 '\"qmd\"'"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":645,"cacheRead":45658,"cacheWrite":390,"totalTokens":46694,"cost":{"input":0.000003,"output":0.009675,"cacheRead":0.0136974,"cacheWrite":0.0014625,"total":0.024837899999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772845956013}}
